main event: On November 8, 1956, a round yellow-orange object, the size of a dime at arm's length, was observed moving upward and to the northwest at moderate speed in Colfax, Iowa.
interesting points: The object was observed visually for one minute,The size of the object was comparable to a dime at arm's length,The object appeared to taper out to a point,The sighting included various possible conclusions such as it being a weather balloon or aircraft,The report includes a reference to notifications sent to intelligence units regarding the sighting.
witness description: Not specified, but the observation was visually made.
